# System Design Overview

## Introduction
The system design phase focuses on defining the structure and functionality of the CareNest System. This includes system behavior, data structure, and user interactions.

## Use Case Diagrams
Use case diagrams were created to represent the interactions between users (Admin and Staff) and the system. These diagrams illustrate key functionalities such as attendance management and medical record handling.

## ER Diagram
The Entity Relationship (ER) diagram defines the database structure of the system. It includes entities such as Child, MedicalRecord, Attendance, and User, along with their relationships.

## Context Diagram
The context diagram represents the system at a high level, showing interactions between external actors and the CareNest System.

## Summary
The system design ensures a structured and scalable solution for managing children’s home operations efficiently.
